{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"40e1b624-2e84-4aee-8d15-85bff1813dc8","content":"Use **`dotnet run`**, not `dotnet test`.\n\nHot reload with `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HotReload` works through the **Microsoft Testing Platform** runner, which is an executable. `dotnet run` launches your test project as an app, enabling the hot reload loop — it watches for file changes and re-runs affected tests automatically.\n\n`dotnet test` does not activate the hot reload pipeline; it uses the traditional VSTest adapter flow.\n\nSo:\n\n```bash\n# Set the env var (if not already)\nexport TESTINGPLATFORM_HOTRELOAD_ENABLED=1\n\n# Run with hot reload\ndotnet run\n```\n\nYour project already has `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` enabled and the HotReload package referenced, so you're all set.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"3bda2414-57cd-44cd-b9ad-32abc1baf0af","outputTokens":183,"requestId":"A810:1D839C:26FBC08:2971A67:6A0493B6"},"id":"6409edfa-9195-4975-b7ad-ba066859bc11","timestamp":"2026-05-13T15:07:45.147Z","parentId":"3c77ce76-efb4-47a7-b7da-070b170a629d"}
